        "instructions": [
            {
                "step": 1,
                "description": "To prepare crust add graham crackers to a food processor and process until you reach fine crumbs. Add melted butter and pulse 3-4 times to coat crumbs with butter." 
            },
            {
                "step": 2,
                "description": "Pour mixture into a 20cm (8‚Äù) tart tin. Use the back of a spoon to firmly press the mixture out across the bottom and sides of the tart tin. Chill for 30 min."
            },
            {
                "step": 3,
                "description": "Begin by adding the marshmallows and melted butter into a microwave safe bowl. Microwave for 30 seconds and mix to combine. Set aside." 
            },
            {
                "step": 4,
                "description": "Next, add the gelatine and water to a small mixing bowl and mix to combine. Microwave for 30 seconds." 
            },
            {
                "step": 5,
                "description": "Add the cream cheese to the marshmallow mixture and use a hand mixer or stand mixer fitted with a paddle attachment to mix until smooth." 
            },
            {
                "step": 6,
                "description": "Add the warm cream and melted gelatin mixture and mix until well combined." 
            },
            {
                "step": 7,
                "description": "Add 1/3 of the mixture to a mixing bowl, add purple food gel and mix until well combined. Colour 1/3 of the mixture blue. Split the remaining mixture into two mixing bowls, colour one pink and leave the other white." 
            },
            {
                "step": 8,
                "description": "Pour half the purple cheesecake mixture into the chill tart crust. Add half the blue and then add the remaining purple and blue in the tart tin. Use a spoon to drizzle some pink cheesecake on top. Use a skewer or the end of a spoon to swirl the pink. Add some small dots of the plain cheesecake mixture to create stars and then sprinkle some more starts on top before chilling for 2 hours." 
            },
            {
                "step": 9,
                "description": "Slice with a knife to serve." 
            }
        ],
